Sales & Rental Property Consultants
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/01 08:41:30
Ref. JB3046216
Job Description
Our Sales & Rental Consultants are expected to demonstrate commitment, loyalty and ability to work well in a team environment.
The Property Consultants role is to act as a representative for clients of Kendal & Co and negotiate the successful sale & rentals of properties, advise property owners on market conditions and strive to fulfill their sales targets set out for them.
We are looking for consultants who are top performers in their marketplace who will uphold our reputation and strong market presence by delivering exceptional customer service.
Kendal & Co offers very attractive commission schemes tailored to each consultant’s experience.
We also offer target incentive packages which include;
I Pads, designer watches and all expenses paid holidays.
The applicant must be ambitious, motivated and strive for a successful career within the real estate industry. UAE real experience is a must, those without need not apply.
Main duties include, but are not limited to:
Key Responsibilities
•	Generate and follow up with leads
•	Buyer and seller consultations
•	Client viewings (this may include weekends and out of working hours)
•	Ability to handle negotiations and contract-to-close activities
•	The applicant must have their own existing network and contacts of buyers and sellers of properties within the UAE
•	Responsible for working in a target driven sales environment
•	Ability to work well within a team environment
•	Sets goals and strives to achieve them with enthusiasm and determination
•	Complete all necessary documentation associated with listing and selling property within the UAE
•	Ensure potential customers are provided with reliable and accurate information regarding properties
•	Attend to sales enquiries and meetings professionally and maintain a high standard of service
•	Source potential clients and establish a good work relationship
Skills
•	Minimum of 1 year UAE real estate experience
•	RERA certified
•	Experience with dealing with high-net worth individuals and VIP clientele
•	Driving license and own vehicle
•	Computer literate in basic software
•	Excellent communication skills in English
•	Willingness to work outside of working hours and on weekends
•	Must have a detailed knowledge of property and contract laws relevant to buying, selling and leasing property.
•	Presentable, confident and driven
•	Good time management skills
•	Assertive and willingness to work independently
•	Good interpersonal skills
